 a manifested UV bump are more\nluminous at rest-frame 8mum, where the emission is dominated by PAHs (also\nproducts of AGB stars). In addition, they exhibit stronger UV absorption\nfeatures, mostly of interstellar origin, which indicates overall more evolved\nstellar populations. We conclude that diversification of the small-size dust\ncomponent has already started in the most evolved star-forming systems at\n1<z<2.5.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 24 Mar 2009 15:00:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 24 Apr 2009 13:32:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-13"}
